properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 7 at 4:34AM PST until January 7 at 9:24PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Seattle has issued a flood warning
for the following rivers in Washington...

Bogachiel River Near La Push affecting Clallam County

4 to 6 inches of rain over the Olympics in the last 36 hours will
cause the Bogachiel river near La Push to go above flood stage this
morning. The river will recede this afternoon.

The National Weather Service in Seattle has issued a

* Flood Warning for
The Bogachiel River Near La Push
* until this evening.
* At  3:30 AM Tuesday the stage was 36.0 feet.
* Flood stage is 37.0 feet.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river will rise above flood stage around 6 AM
Tuesday and crest near 37.4 feet around 7 AM Tuesday. The river
will fall below flood stage early this afternoon.
* Impact...At 37.0 feet, the Bogachiel River will cause flooding of
State Highway 110 near the Bogachiel bridge...closing the road.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
